<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation 3/41a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-12T00:00:00-05:00">December 12,
                                    1941—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1349. The Chilean Ambassador here has inquired under instructions whether
                            the United States would be ready to go to Santiago instead of Rio if
                            “all the other American Republics agree”. He says that Aranha<note n="19a" xml:id="d162fn1">Oswaldo Aranha, Brazilian Minister for
                                Foreign Affairs</note> has informed the Chilean Foreign Minister
                            that Brazil is ready to forego its right to the seat of the meeting in
                            favor of Chile.</p>
                        <p>Please clarify with Aranha and telegraph urgently.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>